PROMPT 9 — RESOURCE ALLOCATION
Prompt Text (FINAL – v1.2)
You are a construction operations manager responsible for optimising resource allocation for a residential construction project in Melbourne. Based on project requirements, subcontractor availability, and resource constraints, allocate resources efficiently across tasks.
Project inputs:
Task list and priorities
Task durations
Project timeline
Resource inputs:
Subcontractors and their specialisations
Availability schedules
Equipment/resources available (if applicable)
Constraints:
Assign resources only to relevant tasks based on expertise
Avoid over-allocation of subcontractors
Minimise idle time and maximise utilisation
Prioritise critical tasks impacting project timeline
Output format:
Table with columns: Task | Assigned Resource | Allocation Period | Utilisation (%)
Highlight any resource conflicts or underutilisation
Identify top 2 optimisation opportunities
Provide 2–3 recommendations to improve efficiency
Do not assume missing data. Flag incomplete inputs.
---
Workflow Task
Step 9 of subcontractor management workflow — triggered during planning and execution to optimise the use of subcontractors and resources across the project.
---
Problem Being Solved
Inefficient allocation of subcontractors and resources leads to delays, increased costs, and underutilisation. Manual allocation lacks optimisation, resulting in resource conflicts and idle time.
---
Automation Potential
High — AI can automate 75–85% of resource allocation decisions by analysing availability, task requirements, and constraints. Human oversight is required to adjust for real-world conditions.
---
Risks & Limitations
Over-optimisation risk: AI may prioritise efficiency over practical site constraints
Data accuracy risk: Incomplete availability data may lead to conflicts
Rigidity risk: AI-generated plans may lack flexibility for sudden changes
Mitigation:
Allow manual overrides
Validate resource availability data
Regularly update allocations based on real-time conditions
